{"id":1053,"date":"2011-10-07T21:17:24","date_gmt":"2011-10-08T01:17:24","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.dailyhadithonline.com\/?p=1053"},"modified":"2023-03-18T02:49:30","modified_gmt":"2023-03-17T22:49:30","slug":"taqwa-in-the-heart","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2011\/10\/07\/taqwa-in-the-heart\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Brotherhood: Do not hate others, righteousness in the heart"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201c<strong>Do not envy each other, do not outbid each other, do not hate each other, do not turn away from each other, and do not outsell each other. Rather, be servants of Allah as brothers. The Muslim is the brother of another Muslim. He does not wrong him, nor humiliate him, nor look down upon him. Righteousness is here,<\/strong>\u201d and he pointed to his chest three times. The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>It is enough evil for a man to look down upon his Muslim brother. The entirety of the Muslim is sacred to another Muslim: his life, his wealth, and his reputation.<\/strong>\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 2564<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <em><strong>Sahih\u00a0<\/strong><\/em>(authentic) according to Muslim<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0647\u064f\u0631\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0631\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0645\u064e \u0644\u064e\u0627 \u062a\u064e\u062d\u064e\u0627\u0633\u064e\u062f\u064f\u0648\u0627 \u0648\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0627 \u062a\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0627\u062c\u064e\u0634\u064f\u0648\u0627 \u0648\u064e\u0